title: JP Marceau on The Trinity, Panpsychism, and Relevance Realization
description:
JP Marceau is a friend I met through the Paul Vanderklay community. He has a background in philosophy with interests in the patristic period of the church fathers, neoplatonism, and Thomism. He combines these old ideas with new philosophical schools of thought like panpsychism and process theology. 

We have an interesting discussion covering many people like John Vervaeke, Jonathan Pageau, Mary Kochan, Bertrand Russell, Henry Bergson, Thomas Aquinas, St Maximus the Confessor, John Scotus Eriugena, Plotinus, Beau Branson, Augustine, Khalil Andani, the Cappacodcian Fathers, Irenaeus of Lyon, Godel's incompleteness theorem, and much more.

Here is JP's youtube channel: https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCZzlvx0HHYiPOJTEOU399WA

Here is JP's talk with Paul Vanderklay: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=M6QmOWI2Ysw

And my favorite talk between JP, Mary, and John: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=baQQQwPAcMY
